g.text: Cameco is the world’s largest publically traded uranium company. The following diagram follows the possible supply chain from the company’s mining locations to their fuel distributon network.

U02 pellets are baked at high temperature
U02 pellets are grounddown to exact size
Finalized U02 pelletsare packed into fuel rods
Fuel rods are grouped into cylindrical bundles for use in CANDU reactors
U is compactedto get a finer consistency
Enriched U02 is pressed into capsules
U02 capsules are baked at high temperature
U02 capsules are grounddown to exact size
Finalized U02 capsuare packed into fuel rodswith higher safety protocols
Fuel rods are snapped together in a fuel assemblyfor use in Light Water reactors
Material is transported from mills, enrichmentfuel manufacturing facilitiesto either maritime shipping portsor directly to nuclear power facilities via semi-truck

International maritime shipping ports acceptshipments of both enriched and unenrichednear fuel. These shipments are then loaded onto semi-trucks or trains and sent to power plants or facilities for further processing
Nuclear Fuel is transported internationallyto either nuclear power plants or to facilitiesfor further manufacturing via container ship.
After being transported to the designatedpower plant, the fuel goes through the various internal systems and processes for power to be generated from the fissile material.

After the fuel is completely spent in the reaction process it is put through multiple levels of storage for different lengths of timebefore being placed in dry storage casks to live for the next millenia.
